Investing_In_Our_Future
[2017 Legislative Goals Met]
****** 2017 Legislative Goals Met ******
Lawmakers passed the largest state &amp; local infrastructure investment in
Indiana's history, supported an honestly balanced, two-year state budget and
funded key priorities. House Republicans successfully passed other legislative
agenda items, including supporting students and teachers, improving Indiana's
workforce, increasing public safety and attacking the state's drug epidemic.
News_Release Road_Funding_Plan

***** Conference Committee Report for HEA 1001 *****
[Conference Committee Report for HEA 1001 ]
House Enrolled Act 1001, Indiana&rsquo;s State Biennial Budget, funds key
priorities while upholding our commitment to fiscal integrity and maintaining
strong reserves.
 Learn_More
***** Tuition Support Formula *****
[Tuition Support Formula]
Tuition support distribution estimates by school. 
 View_the_full_list
***** No. 1 State Government in U.S. *****
[No. 1 State Government in U.S.]
Indiana stands out as the No. 1 state for government administration in the U.S.
News Best States ranking based on fiscal stability, budget transparency,
government digitalization and state integrity.
 Learn_More
***** Standing Committee Assignments *****
[Standing Committee Assignments]
House Speaker Brian C. Bosma announced House standing committee assignments for
the 120th General Assembly. On Jan. 4, House lawmakers will convene at 1:30
p.m. in the House Chamber for the first day of the legislative session.
 View_the_full_list
***** Committee Chairmanships & Leadership Appointments *****
[Committee Chairmanships & Leadership Appointments]
House Speaker Brian C. Bosma announced House committee chairmanships and House
Republican leadership appointments. The House speaker appoints committee chairs
and caucus leaders biennially after each election.
